%% Diagram: KSK Double-DS Rollover Timeline
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Op as Operator
    participant Signer as Zone Signer
    participant Auth as Authoritative NS
    participant Reg as Registrar / Parent
    participant Res as Validating Resolver

    Op->>Signer: Generate new KSK (KSK_new)
    Signer->>Auth: Publish DNSKEY RRset (KSK_old + KSK_new + ZSK)
    Note over Auth,Res: Wait DNSKEY TTL + propagation,<br/>so resolvers see both KSKs.
    Op->>Reg: Submit DS for KSK_new
    Reg->>Reg: Add DS_new alongside DS_old
    Note over Reg,Res: Wait parent DS TTL,<br/>so resolvers see both DS records.
    Op->>Reg: Remove DS_old
    Note over Reg,Res: Wait parent DS TTL again,<br/>so DS_old falls out of caches.
    Op->>Signer: Retire KSK_old
    Signer->>Auth: Publish DNSKEY RRset (KSK_new + ZSK)
    Res->>Auth: Validate via KSK_new → DS_new chain
    Note over Op,Res: RFC 6781 §4.1.2 Double-DS rollover.<br/>Skip a wait step → SERVFAIL outage.
